trans-unit.source: Determines if this doc flavor object is equal to the given object. The two are equal if the given object is not null, is an instance of DocFlavor, has a MIME type equivalent to this doc flavor object's MIME type (that is, the MIME types have the same media type, media subtype, and parameters), and has the same representation class name as this doc flavor object. Thus, if two doc flavor objects' MIME types are the same except for comments, they are considered equal. However, two doc flavor objects with MIME types of "text/plain" and "text/plain; charset=US-ASCII" are not considered equal, even though they represent the same media type (because the default character set for plain text is US-ASCII).
trans-unit.target: 确定此DocFlavor对象是否等于给定的对象。如果给定对象不为 null ，是 DocFlavor 的实例，且MIME类型等于此DocFlavor对象的MIME类型（即MIME类型具有相同的媒体类型，媒体子类型和参数），则两者相等；并具有与此DocFlavor对象相同的表示形式类名称。因此，如果两个文档风味对象的MIME类型（除了注释）相同，则将它们视为相等。但是，两个MIME类型为“文本/纯文本”和“文本/纯文本； charset = US-ASCII”的doc类对象即使它们表示相同的媒体类型，也不认为是相等的（因为纯文本的默认字符集是US-ASCII）。

trans-unit.source: Determines in which direction the next view lays.
trans-unit.target: 确定下一个视图的方向。

trans-unit.source: Determines in which direction the next view lays. Consider the View at index n. Typically the Views are layed out from left to right, so that the View to the EAST will be at index n + 1, and the View to the WEST will be at index n - 1. In certain situations, such as with bidirectional text, it is possible that the View to EAST is not at index n + 1, but rather at index n - 1, or that the View to the WEST is not at index n - 1, but index n + 1. In this case this method would return true, indicating the Views are layed out in descending order.
trans-unit.target: 确定下一个视图的放置方向。考虑索引n处的 View 。通常， View 从左到右排列，以便EAST的 View 位于索引n + 1，而WEST的 View 位于索引n-1。在某些情况下，例如双向文本，则EAST的 View 可能不在索引n + 1处，而是在索引n-1处，或者WEST的 View 不在索引n-1处，而是在索引n + 1处。方法将返回true，指示 View 的布局按降序排列。

trans-unit.source: Determines in which direction the next view lays. Consider the View at index n. Typically the Views are layed out from left to right, so that the View to the EAST will be at index n + 1, and the View to the WEST will be at index n - 1. In certain situations, such as with bidirectional text, it is possible that the View to EAST is not at index n + 1, but rather at index n - 1, or that the View to the WEST is not at index n - 1, but index n + 1. In this case this method would return true, indicating the Views are layed out in descending order. Otherwise the method would return false indicating the Views are layed out in ascending order.
trans-unit.target: 确定下一个视图的放置方向。考虑索引n处的视图。通常， View 从左到右排列，以便EAST的 View 位于索引n + 1，而WEST的 View 位于索引n-1。在某些情况下，例如双向文本，则EAST的 View 可能不在索引n + 1处，而是在索引n-1处，或者WEST的 View 不在索引n-1处，而是在索引n + 1处。方法将返回true，指示 View 的布局按降序排列。否则，该方法将返回false，指示 View 的布局按升序排列。

trans-unit.source: Determines the date and time based on the arguments. The arguments are interpreted as a year, month, day of the month, hour of the day, minute within the hour, and second within the minute, exactly as for the Date constructor with six arguments, except that the arguments are interpreted relative to UTC rather than to the local time zone. The time indicated is returned represented as the distance, measured in milliseconds, of that time from the epoch (00:00:00 GMT on January 1, 1970).
trans-unit.target: 根据参数确定日期和时间。参数解释为年，月，月，日，小时，小时内的分钟，以及分钟内的秒，与具有六个参数的 Date 构造函数完全一样，只是参数是相对于UTC解释的而不是本地时区。返回指示的时间，该时间表示距该时间点（从1970年1月1日格林尼治标准时间00:00:00）到该时间的距离（以毫秒为单位）。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether a compound name is a suffix of this compound name.

trans-unit.target: 确定一个复合名是否是这个复合名的后缀。如果复名'n'等于getSuffix(size()-n.size())--换句话说,这个复名以'n'结尾,那么它就是一个后缀。如果n为空或不是复名,则返回false。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether a compound name is a suffix of this compound name. A compound name 'n' is a suffix if it it is equal to getSuffix(size()-n.size())--in other words, this compound name ends with 'n'. If n is null or not a compound name, false is returned.
trans-unit.target: 确定一个复合名是否是这个复合名的后缀。如果复合名'n'等于getSuffix(size()-n.size()),那么它就是一个后缀--换句话说,这个复合名以'n'结束。如果n为空或不是复名,则返回false。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether a type can be converted to another without losing any precision. As a special case, void is considered convertible only to void and Object (either as null or as a custom value set in DynamicLinkerFactory.setAutoConversionStrategy(MethodTypeConversionStrategy)). Somewhat unintuitively, we consider anything to be convertible to void even though converting to void causes the ultimate loss of data. On the other hand, conversion to void essentially means that the value is of no interest and should be discarded, thus there's no expectation of preserving any precision.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否可以在不损失任何精度的情况下将一种类型转换为另一种类型。作为一种特殊情况，void被认为只能转换为void和 Object （可以为 null 或作为 DynamicLinkerFactory.setAutoConversionStrategy(MethodTypeConversionStrategy) 中设置的自定义值）。有点不直观，即使转换为空会导致数据的最终丢失，我们还是认为任何东西都可以转换为空。另一方面，转换为void本质上意味着该值无关紧要，应该将其丢弃，因此不希望保留任何精度。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether a value is in the attribute.

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is a reference with the same addresses (in same order) as this reference.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否是一个地址与这个引用相同(顺序相同)的引用。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is a reference with the same addresses (in same order) as this reference. The addresses are checked using RefAddr.equals(). In addition to having the same addresses, the Reference also needs to have the same class name as this reference. The class factory and class factory location are not checked. If obj is null or not an instance of Reference, null is returned.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否是一个地址与这个引用相同(顺序相同)的引用。使用RefAddr.equals()检查地址。除了拥有相同的地址外,Reference还需要拥有与这个引用相同的类名。不检查类工厂和类工厂的位置。如果obj为空或不是Reference的实例,则返回null。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is equal to this RefAddr.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否等于这个RefAddr。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is equal to this address.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否等于这个地址。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is equal to this address. It is equal if it contains the same address type and their contents are byte-wise equivalent.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否等于这个地址。如果包含相同的地址类型,并且它们的内容在字节上是相等的,则为相等。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is equal to this attribute.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否等于该属性。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is equal to this attribute. Two attributes are equal if their attribute-ids, syntaxes and values are equal. If the attribute values are unordered, the order that the values were added are irrelevant. If the attribute values are ordered, then the order the values must match. If obj is null or not an Attribute, false is returned.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否等于这个属性。如果两个属性的属性id、语法和值都相等,则两个属性相等。如果属性值是无序的,那么属性值添加的顺序就无关紧要。如果属性值是有序的,那么值的顺序必须匹配。如果obj为空或不是属性,则返回false。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is syntactically equal to this compound name.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否在语法上等于这个复合名。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether obj is syntactically equal to this compound name. If obj is null or not a CompoundName, false is returned. Two compound names are equal if each component in one is "equal" to the corresponding component in the other.
trans-unit.target: 确定obj是否在语法上等于这个复合名。如果obj为空或不是CompoundName,则返回false。如果两个复名中的每个成分都等于另一个复名中的相应成分,则表示两个复名相等。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether objects will be returned as part of the result.
trans-unit.target: 确定对象是否会作为结果的一部分被返回。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether one type can be converted to another type using a method invocation conversion, as per JLS 5.3 "Method Invocation Conversion".
trans-unit.target: 根据JLS 5.3 "方法调用转换",确定一个类型是否可以通过方法调用转换转换为另一个类型。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether one type can be converted to another type using a method invocation conversion, as per JLS 5.3 "Method Invocation Conversion". This is basically all conversions allowed by subtyping (see isSubtype(Class, Class)) as well as boxing conversion (JLS 5.1.7) optionally followed by widening reference conversion, and unboxing conversion (JLS 5.1.8) optionally followed by widening primitive conversion.
trans-unit.target: 根据JLS 5.3“方法调用转换”，确定是否可以使用方法调用转换将一种类型转换为另一种类型。这基本上是子类型化（请参见 isSubtype(Class, Class) ）以及装箱转换（JLS 5.1.7）允许的所有转换，还可以选择加宽引用转换，以及装箱转换（JLS 5.1.8），可以选择加宽原始转换。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether one type is a subtype of another type, as per JLS 4.10 "Subtyping".
trans-unit.target: 根据JLS 4.10 "Subtyping",确定一个类型是否是另一个类型的子类型。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether one type is a subtype of another type, as per JLS 4.10 "Subtyping". Note: this is not strict or proper subtype, therefore true is also returned for identical types; to be completely precise, it allows identity conversion (JLS 5.1.1), widening primitive conversion (JLS 5.1.2) and widening reference conversion (JLS 5.1.5).
trans-unit.target: 根据 JLS 4.10 "Subtyping" 确定一个类型是否是另一个类型的子类型。注意:这不是严格的子类型,因此对于相同的类型,也会返回 true;准确地说,它允许身份转换 (JLS 5.1.1),加宽基元转换 (JLS 5.1.2)和加宽引用转换 (JLS 5.1.5)。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not a given file object is "contained in" a specified location.
trans-unit.target: 确定给定的文件对象是否 "包含在 "指定的位置。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not ends of line are treated as tokens.
trans-unit.target: 确定线的末端是否作为标记处理。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not ends of line are treated as tokens. If the flag argument is true, this tokenizer treats end of lines as tokens; the nextToken method returns TT_EOL and also sets the ttype field to this value when an end of line is read.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否将行尾视为标记。如果flag参数为true，则此标记化程序将行尾视为标记；否则，标记符将无效。所述 nextToken 方法返回 TT_EOL 并且还设置 ttype 字段到该值时，读取线的端部。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the interior of the arc entirely contains the specified rectangle.
trans-unit.target: 确定弧的内部是否完全包含指定的矩形。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the interior of the arc intersects the interior of the specified rectangle.
trans-unit.target: 确定弧的内部是否与指定的矩形内部相交。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the root node from the TreeModel is visible.

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the root node from the TreeModel is visible.
trans-unit.target: 确定TreeModel中的根节点是否可见。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the specified Object is equal to this Arc2D.
trans-unit.target: 确定指定的 Object 是否等于此 Arc2D 。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the specified Object is equal to this Arc2D. The specified Object is equal to this Arc2D if it is an instance of Arc2D and if its location, size, arc extents and type are the same as this Arc2D.
trans-unit.target: 确定指定的 Object 是否等于此 Arc2D 。指定的 Object 等于此 Arc2D 如果是的一个实例 Arc2D ，如果它的位置，大小，电弧程度和类型是相同的，因为这 Arc2D 。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the specified Object is equal to this Ellipse2D.

trans-unit.target: 确定指定的 Object 是否等于此 Ellipse2D 。指定的 Object 等于此 Ellipse2D 的，如果它是一个实例 Ellipse2D 的，如果它的位置和大小是相同的，因为这 Ellipse2D 的。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the specified Object is equal to this Rectangle2D.
trans-unit.target: 确定指定的 Object 是否等于此 Rectangle2D 。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the specified Object is equal to this Rectangle2D. The specified Object is equal to this Rectangle2D if it is an instance of Rectangle2D and if its location and size are the same as this Rectangle2D.
trans-unit.target: 确定指定的 Object 是否等于此 Rectangle2D 。指定的 Object 等于此 Rectangle2D 如果是的实例 Rectangle2D ，并且如果它的位置和大小是相同的，因为这 Rectangle2D 。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the specified Object is equal to this RoundRectangle2D.

trans-unit.target: 确定指定的 Object 是否等于此 RoundRectangle2D 。如果指定的 Object 是 RoundRectangle2D 的实例，并且其位置，大小和角弧尺寸与此 RoundRectangle2D RoundRectangle2D ，则指定的Object等于此RoundRectangle2D。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the specified angle is within the angular extents of the arc.
trans-unit.target: 判断指定的角度是否在圆弧的角度范围内。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the tokenizer recognizes C++-style comments.
trans-unit.target: 决定tokenizer是否能识别C++风格的注释。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the tokenizer recognizes C++-style comments. If the flag argument is true, this stream tokenizer recognizes C++-style comments. Any occurrence of two consecutive slash characters ('/') is treated as the beginning of a comment that extends to the end of the line.
trans-unit.target: 确定令牌生成器是否识别C ++样式的注释。如果flag参数为 true ，则此流标记器识别C ++样式的注释。任何出现的两个连续的斜杠字符（ '/' ）都将被视为注释的开始，该注释延伸到该行的末尾。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the tokenizer recognizes C-style comments.
trans-unit.target: 确定tokenizer是否能识别C式注释。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not the tokenizer recognizes C-style comments. If the flag argument is true, this stream tokenizer recognizes C-style comments. All text between successive occurrences of /* and */ are discarded.
trans-unit.target: 确定分词器是否识别C样式的注释。如果flag参数为 true ，则此流标记器识别C样式的注释。连续出现的 /* 和 */ 之间的所有文本都将被丢弃。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not this Rectangle and the specified Rectangle intersect.
trans-unit.target: 确定此 Rectangle 与指定 Rectangle 是否相交。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not this Rectangle and the specified Rectangle intersect. Two rectangles intersect if their intersection is nonempty.
trans-unit.target: 确定此 Rectangle 与指定 Rectangle 是否相交。如果两个矩形的交集为非空，则它们相交。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not this node is allowed to have children.
trans-unit.target: 确定此节点是否允许有子节点。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not this node is allowed to have children. If allows is false, all of this node's children are removed.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否允许此节点具有子级。如果 allows 为false，则删除此节点的所有子节点。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not to allow access to the guarded object object.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否允许访问受保护对象 object 。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not to allow access to the guarded object object. Returns silently if access is allowed. Otherwise, throws a SecurityException.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否允许访问受保护对象 object 。如果允许访问，则以静默方式返回。否则，抛出SecurityException。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not two points are equal.
trans-unit.target: 判断两点是否相等。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not two points are equal. Two instances of Point2D are equal if the values of their x and y member fields, representing their position in the coordinate space, are the same.
trans-unit.target: 确定两个点是否相等。如果 Point2D 的两个实例的 x 和 y 成员字段的值（表示它们在坐标空间中的位置）相同，则它们相等。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not word token are automatically lowercased.
trans-unit.target: 决定字词是否自动小写。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether or not word token are automatically lowercased. If the flag argument is true, then the value in the sval field is lowercased whenever a word token is returned (the ttype field has the value TT_WORD by the nextToken method of this tokenizer.
trans-unit.target: 确定单词标记是否自动小写。如果flag参数为 true ，则每当返回单词令牌时， sval 字段中的值都将小写（此令牌 ttype 的 nextToken 方法的ttype字段值为 TT_WORD 。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the AcceptAll FileFilter is used as an available choice in the choosable filter list.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否将 AcceptAll FileFilter 用作可选过滤器列表中的可用选项。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the AcceptAll FileFilter is used as an available choice in the choosable filter list. If false, the AcceptAll file filter is removed from the list of available file filters. If true, the AcceptAll file filter will become the actively used file filter.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否将 AcceptAll FileFilter 用作可选过滤器列表中的可用选项。如果为false， AcceptAll 可用文件过滤器列表中删除AcceptAll文件过滤器。如果为true， AcceptAll 文件过滤器将成为活动使用的文件过滤器。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the JComboBox field is editable.
trans-unit.target: 确定 JComboBox 字段是否可编辑。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the JComboBox field is editable. An editable JComboBox allows the user to type into the field or selected an item from the list to initialize the field, after which it can be edited. (The editing affects only the field, the list item remains intact.) A non editable JComboBox displays the selected item in the field, but the selection cannot be modified.
trans-unit.target: 确定 JComboBox 字段是否可编辑。可编辑的 JComboBox 允许用户在该字段中键入或从列表中选择一个项目以初始化该字段，然后可以对其进行编辑。（编辑仅影响该字段，列表项保持不变。）不可编辑的 JComboBox 将在该字段中显示选定的项目，但是无法修改选择。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the JSplitPane is set to use a continuous layout.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否将 JSplitPane 设置为使用连续布局。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the RectangularShape is empty.
trans-unit.target: 确定 RectangularShape 是否为空。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the RectangularShape is empty. When the RectangularShape is empty, it encloses no area.
trans-unit.target: 确定 RectangularShape 是否为空。当 RectangularShape 为空时，它不包含任何区域。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the access request indicated by the specified permission should be allowed or denied, based on the current AccessControlContext and security policy.
trans-unit.target: 根据当前的 AccessControlContext 和安全策略,决定是否允许或拒绝指定权限所指示的访问请求。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the access request indicated by the specified permission should be allowed or denied, based on the current AccessControlContext and security policy. This method quietly returns if the access request is permitted, or throws an AccessControlException otherwise. The getPermission method of the AccessControlException returns the perm Permission object instance.
trans-unit.target: 根据当前的AccessControlContext和安全策略，确定是应允许还是拒绝由指定权限指示的访问请求。如果允许访问请求，则此方法安静地返回，否则，将抛出AccessControlException。AccessControlException的getPermission方法返回 perm 许可对象实例。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the access request indicated by the specified permission should be allowed or denied, based on the security policy currently in effect, and the context in this object.
trans-unit.target: 根据当前有效的安全策略和该对象中的上下文,决定是否允许或拒绝指定权限所指示的访问请求。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the access request indicated by the specified permission should be allowed or denied, based on the security policy currently in effect, and the context in this object. The request is allowed only if every ProtectionDomain in the context implies the permission. Otherwise the request is denied.
trans-unit.target: 根据当前有效的安全策略和此对象中的上下文,决定是否允许或拒绝指定权限所指示的访问请求。只有当上下文中的每一个ProtectionDomain都包含该权限时,请求才会被允许。否则请求将被拒绝。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the action should be performed with the specified sender object.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否应该对指定的发送对象执行操作。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the action should be performed with the specified sender object. The sender can be null. The method must return false if the action is disabled.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否应使用指定的发送者对象执行操作。该 sender 可以为 null 。如果禁用该操作，则该方法必须返回false。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the attribute set ignores the case of attribute identifiers when retrieving or adding attributes.
trans-unit.target: 确定属性集在检索或添加属性时是否忽略属性标识符的情况。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the authentication exchange has completed.
trans-unit.target: 确定认证交换是否已经完成。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the authentication exchange has completed. This method is typically called after each invocation of evaluateResponse() to determine whether the authentication has completed successfully or should be continued.
trans-unit.target: 确定认证交换是否已完成。通常在每次调用 evaluateResponse() 之后调用此方法，以确定身份验证是成功完成还是应该继续进行。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the authentication exchange has completed. This method may be called at any time, but typically, it will not be called until the caller has received indication from the server (in a protocol-specific manner) that the exchange has completed.
trans-unit.target: 确定认证交换是否已经完成。这个方法可以在任何时候被调用,但一般情况下,在调用者收到服务器(以特定协议的方式)发出的交换已经完成的指示之前,不会被调用。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the authentication id is allowed to act on behalf of the authorization id.
trans-unit.target: 确定是否允许认证id代表授权id行事。

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the character is mirrored according to the Unicode specification.

trans-unit.source: Device coordinates are defined to be between device pixels which avoids any inconsistent results between aliased and antialiased rendering. If coordinates were defined to be at a pixel's center, some of the pixels covered by a shape, such as a rectangle, would only be half covered. With aliased rendering, the half covered pixels would either be rendered inside the shape or outside the shape. With anti-aliased rendering, the pixels on the entire edge of the shape would be half covered. On the other hand, since coordinates are defined to be between pixels, a shape like a rectangle would have no half covered pixels, whether or not it is rendered using antialiasing.
trans-unit.target: 设备坐标被定义在设备像素之间,这就避免了别名和反别名渲染之间的不一致结果。如果坐标被定义在一个像素的中心,那么形状(如矩形)所覆盖的一些像素将只被覆盖一半。使用别名渲染时,被覆盖一半的像素将被渲染在形状内或形状外。在反锯齿渲染中,形状的整个边缘的像素将被覆盖一半。另一方面,由于坐标被定义在像素之间,所以像矩形这样的形状,无论是否使用抗锯齿渲染,都不会有半覆盖的像素。

trans-unit.source: Direct instances of this class may be used to implement simple caches; this class or derived subclasses may also be used in larger data structures to implement more sophisticated caches. As long as the referent of a soft reference is strongly reachable, that is, is actually in use, the soft reference will not be cleared. Thus a sophisticated cache can, for example, prevent its most recently used entries from being discarded by keeping strong referents to those entries, leaving the remaining entries to be discarded at the discretion of the garbage collector.

trans-unit.source: Don't confuse the ColorSupported attribute with the Chromaticity attribute. Chromaticity is an attribute the client can specify for a job to tell the printer whether to print a document in monochrome or color, possibly causing the printer to print a color document in monochrome. ColorSupported is a printer description attribute that tells whether the printer can print in color regardless of how the client specifies to print any particular document.
trans-unit.target: 不要混淆 ColorSupported 属性和 Chromaticity 属性。 Chromaticity 是客户端可以为作业指定的属性，以告知打印机是用单色还是彩色打印文档，这可能导致打印机用单色打印彩色文档。 ColorSupported 是打印机描述属性，它告诉打印机是否可以彩色打印，而不管客户端指定如何打印任何特定文档。
